**Code Explanation:**

This script performs the crossover analysis from ballistic to anomalous diffusion for all datasets. It replaces the unreliable Mean Squared Displacement (MSD) with a robust fractional moment of order q=0.2, defined as spread(tau) = <|x(tau)|^q>^(1/q), which converges for all alpha > 0.2. The local scaling exponent H(tau) is calculated as the derivative of the log of this spread measure with respect to log tau. The script identifies the crossover time tau_c where H(tau) drops below 0.85, computes the persistence of the ballistic front to distinguish between Lévy walks and Lévy flights, and generates plots comparing the local H(tau) against theoretical expectations. The theoretical H values are calculated based on the specific mechanism parameters for each dataset.

